
'''Freenode is an internet relay chat (IRC) network. It's for online chatrooms. We hang out in the #p2pf channel. You can join in using your web browser, and there's a read-only archive.'''

URL if you have IRC client already installed = irc://irc.freenode.net/#p2pf

Web access: https://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=p2pf

General information about IRC: http://www.irchelp.org/

The searchable logs are at: http://irc.tiki.org/irclogger_logs/p2pf   This is provided by the Tiki community server infrastructure, so the branding is not strictly for p2pf. If and when the p2p Foundation decides to set up its own logging system, the data will be transferred.

